{"id":"5e9bf7a08fb2d30d7769c765","title":"Introducing: Love Glow","content":"<p><strong><em>Honey</em></strong>, the debut EP from San Diego quartet <strong>Love Glow</strong> was one of the most underrated releases of 2017, and deserved far more acclaim than it’s received so far.</p><p> Merging early 90’s influences, such as The Cardigans and Pale Saints with flecks of more contemporary acts like Wolf Alice, the five track release is a bold first step for the outfit. EP stand out track <em>Better</em> arguably wouldn’t be out of place on Wolf Alice’s critically acclaimed Visions of a Life, whereas the romantic Velvet has all the makes of a indie pop ballad in waiting, yet both still manage to carve out their own niche. Check out a couple of tracks below, and the full EP <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/album/69nLc7SRLLVYv5fkJ46xOr\">here</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/338470617&color=%23ff5500&auto_play=false&hide_related=false&show_comments=true&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=true&visual=true\" width=\"100%\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"no\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/338470625&color=%23ff5500&auto_play=false&hide_related=false&show_comments=true&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=true&visual=true\" width=\"100%\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"no\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/338470619&color=%23ff5500&auto_play=false&hide_related=false&show_comments=true&show_user=true&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=true&visual=true\" width=\"100%\" height=\"300\" frameborder=\"no\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe></p>\n","slug":"34098-introducing-love-glow","category":"introducing","date":1515502905000,"wpid":34098,"isSticky":false,"featured_image":{"width":960,"height":960,"src":"2018/01/20031694_1317236